# Local Storage ðŸ“¦

The way to store data in the browser (no expiration).

```javascript
// Store
localStorage.setItem("lastname", "Smith");

// Retrieve
let name = localStorage.getItem("lastname");

// Remove
localStorage.removeItem("lastname");
```
Data is stored as Strings. Use `JSON.stringify` and `JSON.parse` for objects.

# Geolocation ðŸ“

Get the user's geographical position.

Note: For privacy reasons, the user is asked for permission to report location information.

```javascript
navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(success, error);

function success(position) {
  const lat = position.coords.latitude;
  const lng = position.coords.longitude;
  console.log(`Lat: ${lat}, Lng: ${lng}`);
}
```

# JSON Methods ðŸ› ï¸

Convert between JSON strings and JS Objects.

```javascript
const obj = { name: "John", age: 30 };

// Object to String (for storage/sending)
const myJSON = JSON.stringify(obj);

// String to Object (reading/receiving)
const myObj = JSON.parse(myJSON);
```

# History API ðŸ”™

Interact with the browser's session history.

```javascript
// Go back
window.history.back();

// Go forward
window.history.forward();

// Go to specific point
window.history.go(-2);
```
Crucial for Single Page Applications (SPAs).

# Notifications ðŸ””

Display native system notifications.

Requires permission.

```javascript
Notification.requestPermission().then(permission => {
  if (permission === "granted") {
    new Notification("Hello World!");
  }
});
```

# Local Storage Manager ðŸ’»

<!-- FULL_CODE_START
// Check if supported
if (typeof(Storage) !== "undefined") {
  // Store
  localStorage.setItem("theme", "Dark Mode");

  // Retrieve
  const theme = localStorage.getItem("theme");
  console.log("Saved Theme: " + theme);

  // Complex Data
  const settings = { volume: 50, lang: "en" };
  localStorage.setItem("settings", JSON.stringify(settings));

  // Retrieve Complex Data
  const loadedSettings = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("settings"));
  console.log("Volume:", loadedSettings.volume);
} else {
  console.log("No Web Storage support.");
}
